  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Untreated ankle sprains often remain symptomatic and may end in chronic instability. The aim
      of our study is to quantify the stabilizing effect of different devices. Through the use of a
      foot measurement model in 3D motion analysis the influence of the devices with respect to a
      mechanical effect is examined by means of different tests. The dynamic postural control is
      quantified. The hypothesis was that the devices would stabilize differently the foot
      segments.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
